VijayantaSharmaMarineSuperintendentMaster MarinerISM CodeIRS/ISM/2013/01/01/0328th January 2013YesNoNoMr. AzianshaAspaHSEQASuperintendentNILISM and ISPS Code-24th March 2016YesYesNo13.6ANNEX 6 IT DEPARTMENT PROCEDURESThe following are the guidelines for the IT Department so as to ensure:a. Safety of staffb. That computer hardware and software is properly maintained onboard and ashorec. That data is protected and can be recovered in case of any incident.1 Are all personnel in the department are to be aware of the hazards of handling of electrical equipment and precautions are takenaccordingly.2 Are all software used in the office and onboard shall be either licensed or ‘free to use’ software. Pirated/ unlicensed software shallnot be used.3 Daily back-up shall be taken of the following office data: - Email - Files & Folders - PHOENIXThe back-up data shall be stored at a location which is physically separate (in a separate building) from the servers.4 Regular Anti-virus updates are to be provided to: - Ships (Monthly) - Offices (Singapore and Field offices) – Weekly5 Maintenance shall be carried out on all office systems as recommended by the makers.6 Six monthly inventories are to be taken and being maintained of IT assets of: - Ships - Office7 All machinery parts (of Computer, fax, copier, etc.) are to be disposed of in an environmental friendly manner.8 Emergency room equipment checks are to be carried out monthly and recorded.13.7ANNEX 7 TRAINING AND QUALIFICATIONS MATRIXA.
